                        <repository>DHARMAbase</repository>
                        <idno/>
                    </msIdentifier>
                    <msContents>
                        <summary>
                            Three lists of <foreign>biruda</foreign>s engraved respectively on the three upper tiers (out of four tiers) of the bases of the chapels (also designated as cells or shrines in secondary literature) of the <foreign>prākāra</foreign>. Four <foreign>biruda</foreign>s per chapel, except chapels <seg rend="check">19 or 20</seg> and <seg rend="check">37 or 38</seg>. The lists are the same except for the script (plain Siddhamātr̥kā for the first list, plain Grantha for the second list, ornate Grantha for the third list) and some minor variants. For the fourth tier, see inscription <ref target="DHARMA_INSPallava00056.xml">Pallava 56</ref>.
                            
                            
                            This list no. 4 is shorter than than the lists nos. 1-3 since its ornate Siddhamātr̥kā requires more space that the the scripts of the other lists. Only the chapels nos. <seg rend="check">1-20</seg> are inscribed on this tier. For the first, second and third tiers, see inscription <ref target="DHARMA_INSPallava00055.xml">Pallava 55</ref>. See also inscription <ref target="DHARMA_INSPallava00385.xml">Pallava 385</ref> on the base of the <foreign>prākāra</foreign> of the Mahendreśvara.
                        </summary>
                    </msContents>
                    <physDesc>
                        <handDesc>
                            <p/>
                        </handDesc>
                    </physDesc>
                </msDesc>
            </sourceDesc>
